				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ w_{q} = \frac{1}{{N_{q} }}. $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M8" display="block"><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>w</mml:mi><mml:mi>q</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mfrac><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:msub><mml:mi>N</mml:mi><mml:mi>q</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mfrac><mml:mo>.</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math><graphic xlink:href="13072_2019_321_Article_Equa.gif" position="anchor"/></alternatives></disp-formula>
</p>
      <p id="Par37">Additional file <xref rid="MOESM1" ref-type="media">1</xref>: Figure S3 illustrates the effect of inverse quantile weighting on the YRI beta-values at cg21226234 probe.</p>
      <p id="Par38">The gap between clusters can be defined as the difference in methylation levels between the bordering samples in each cluster, for instance gap between clusters <inline-formula id="IEq4"><alternatives><tex-math id="M9">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
