				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ {\text{gap}}\_{\text{ratio}} $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M20"><mml:mrow><mml:mtext>gap</mml:mtext><mml:mi>_</mml:mi><mml:mtext>ratio</mml:mtext></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13072_2019_321_Article_IEq8.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> value. The <inline-formula id="IEq9"><alternatives><tex-math id="M21">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ {\text{gap}}\_{\text{sum}}\_{\text{ratio}} $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M22"><mml:mrow><mml:mtext>gap</mml:mtext><mml:mi>_</mml:mi><mml:mtext>sum</mml:mtext><mml:mi>_</mml:mi><mml:mtext>ratio</mml:mtext></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13072_2019_321_Article_IEq9.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> approach evaluates the total gap size by summing the size of the gaps and testing whether it represents a majority of the <italic>β</italic>-value range. By contrast, the <inline-formula id="IEq10"><alternatives><tex-math id="M23">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ {\text{gap}}\_{\text{ratio}} $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M24"><mml:mrow><mml:mtext>gap</mml:mtext><mml:mi>_</mml:mi><mml:mtext>ratio</mml:mtext></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13072_2019_321_Article_IEq10.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> approach compares sizes among the two largest gap regions and tests whether their relative sizes are roughly equivalent. To pass this threshold, the size of the smaller gap must be at least a certain percentage of the larger gap. For example, if the <inline-formula id="IEq11"><alternatives><tex-math id="M25">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
